After a spike in covid cases, India has put in place strict restrictions on inbound travel. The WHO has also declared it a pandemic after more than 200,000 confirmed cases and over 8,900 deaths in 114 countries.

India has confirmed three coronavirus deaths so far.

India has suspended "all existing visas, except diplomatic, official, UN/international organisations, employment, project visas" until April 15.

